'''Anders Söderholm''' (born October 26, 1961 in [[Morjärv]], [[Sweden]])<ref name=miun_Anders>{{cite web|title=Anders Söderholm |url=http://www.miun.se/sv/Forskning/Vara-forskare/Forskarportratt/Anders-Soderholm/ |publisher=Mittuniversitetet |accessdate=10 October 2011 |author=Debora Karlsson |language=Swedish |date=2008-04-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513162112/http://www.miun.se/sv/Forskning/Vara-forskare/Forskarportratt/Anders-Soderholm/ |archivedate=13 May 2011 }}</ref> is the current [[Rector (academia)|rector]] of the [[Mid Sweden University]]<ref name=miun_Anders/> and was a [[professor]] in [[Business administration]] at [[Umeå School of Business]].
Söderholm obtained his [[PhD]] from [[Umeå University]] in 1991, with his [[thesis]] on organization of local industrial policies.<ref>{{cite book|last=Söderholm|first=Anders|title=Organiseringens logik : en studie av kommunal näringslivspolitik|year=1991|publisher=Umeå Universitet|location=Umeå|isbn=91-7174-572-6|url=http://libris.kb.se/bib/7615797?vw=full}}</ref> On 2005 he became [[professor]] of [[business administration]]. Söderholm has also been a guest researcher at [[Stanford University]], [[Royal Institute of Technology]] and [[Åbo Akademi University]] and is the [[chairman]] of [http://www.projektakademien.se/pa/?page_id=1045 The Swedish Project Academy].<ref name=rector_blog /> He was the [[Rector (academia)|rector]] of the [[Umeå School of Business]] between 2000-2003.<ref name=rector_blog>{{cite web|title=Rektors blogg |url=http://www.miun.se/sv/Bloggportalen/rektorsblogg/ |publisher=Mittuniversitetet |accessdate=10 October 2011 |author=Anders Söderholm |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120124185837/http://www.miun.se/sv/Bloggportalen/rektorsblogg/ |archivedate=24 January 2012 }}</ref>

